<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=10878&amp;p=123696#p123696"><![CDATA[
It does seem that standard 'fluid' animation on NES (Moon Crystal, for example) uses the on fours, i.e. 15 FPS.<br /><br />It should be noted that 24 FPS is not really a standard animated film rate. The film itself runs at 24 FPS, but the cel changes rarely gets that fluid, for the most part it is on twos or threes, i.e. 12 or 8 cel changes per second.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=4205">Shiru</a> — Sun Jan 12, 2014 2:20 pm</p><hr />
