<div class="quotetitle">koitsu wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><br />Here's my terse response: why would you want this?<br /></div><br />Especially when movements from one cel to the next in 8-bit games are small enough that anything more than the 12 fps cartoon standard wouldn't provide a noticeable enough smoothness benefit to justify its ROM cost. Animate at 12.02 fps (5 field pulldown) on NTSC or 12.50 fps (4 field pulldown) on PAL and you should be fine.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Sat Jan 11, 2014 2:38 pm</p><hr />
